WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:02.750
BOORMAN: <i>I'm begging you, let me do this.</i>

00:02.833 --> 00:05.208
- JADE: We're rescuing Willow.
- And Kit.

00:05.291 --> 00:07.083
ELORA: <i>And all the other people they took.</i>

00:10.041 --> 00:13.541
- ALLAGASH: <i>You're Willow.</i>
- WILLOW: <i>And you're not Madmartigan.</i>

00:13.625 --> 00:14.708
SARRIS: Hi there.

00:14.791 --> 00:18.375
Which one of you is Elora Danan?

00:18.458 --> 00:20.041
(ALL GRUNTING)

00:23.000 --> 00:24.833
Mads tracked me down after 20 years,

00:24.916 --> 00:26.875
asked me to join him
for one more adventure.

00:26.958 --> 00:29.291
- KIT:<i> To find the Cuirass.</i>
- Here. (LAUGHS)

00:29.375 --> 00:31.291
<i>I put the Lux in and nothing.</i>

00:31.375 --> 00:34.125
There's only one way to find out
if it'll work for you, kid.

00:34.708 --> 00:37.250
MADMARTIGAN: (ECHOING)
<i>Kit. Can you hear me?</i>

00:37.333 --> 00:39.875
ALLAGASH: <i>Your father went off</i>
<i>to fight whatever's down there</i>

00:39.958 --> 00:43.333
<i>'cause he believed one of you</i>
<i>would protect what matters most up here.</i>

00:43.416 --> 00:44.916
What matters most?

00:45.000 --> 00:46.583
Elora Danan.

00:46.666 --> 00:48.041
Now get outta here.

00:48.125 --> 00:51.333
- (YELLING)
- (TROLLS SCREECHING)

00:51.416 --> 00:52.583
I could've brought him back,

00:52.666 --> 00:57.458
and I could've finally understood
why every time he chose you instead of me!

00:57.541 --> 00:58.750
(CRASHES)

00:58.833 --> 01:00.000
Your vision.

01:00.083 --> 01:01.791
You saw her fight the Crone.

01:01.875 --> 01:06.541
WILLOW: <i>No matter what I do,</i>
<i>for our world to survive, she has to die.</i>

01:06.625 --> 01:08.000
WOMAN: Anybody out there?

01:08.916 --> 01:10.333
Anybody?

01:11.000 --> 01:12.916
Are you gonna...

01:13.583 --> 01:14.750
let me out?

01:26.208 --> 01:29.291
(CAPTIVATING MUSIC PLAYING)

01:45.125 --> 01:46.125
How long?

01:46.250 --> 01:48.833
(WIND WHOOSHING)

01:48.916 --> 01:50.458
AIRK: The light changes.

01:50.541 --> 01:51.833
The weather... The...

01:51.916 --> 01:54.666
The clouds move too fast.

01:56.208 --> 01:57.416
(SIGHS)

01:57.500 --> 01:58.833
The sun never sets,

02:00.875 --> 02:02.250
this day never ends.

02:03.125 --> 02:05.083
It will, eventually.

02:08.333 --> 02:09.458
How do you know that?

02:09.541 --> 02:11.625
'Cause nothing lasts forever.

02:17.791 --> 02:20.500
It's okay, you can drink it.

02:20.583 --> 02:24.875
I don't know why it's that color
but it tastes... good.

02:24.958 --> 02:26.375
WOMAN: You drank it?

02:29.291 --> 02:30.583
Mmm-hmm.

02:33.083 --> 02:34.083
(GROANS)

02:42.375 --> 02:43.416
(SIGHS)

02:50.625 --> 02:53.500
(SIGHING)

02:55.708 --> 02:57.500
S... So, where are you from?

02:58.750 --> 02:59.750
WOMAN: Cashmere.

03:00.083 --> 03:01.333
AIRK: Oh, really?

03:01.416 --> 03:02.708
(GRUNTS) I'm from Tir Asleen.

03:05.458 --> 03:08.375
- Which is a kingdom in the Vale...
- I know where it is.

03:08.458 --> 03:10.333
Oh. Right. Sure.

03:12.291 --> 03:13.625
(SIGHS)

03:14.500 --> 03:18.125
I'm actually the prince of Tir Asleen.

03:18.625 --> 03:19.666
Congratulations.

03:20.416 --> 03:22.250
Oh, no. (LAUGHS) I didn't... I wasn't...

03:22.333 --> 03:24.875
I was saying that I think
that maybe that's why I'm here.

03:24.958 --> 03:26.125
Are you at war?

03:26.208 --> 03:27.250
No.

03:27.333 --> 03:30.083
(SIGHS) Or...
Well, we weren't when I left.

03:31.291 --> 03:33.083
Well, then who'd kidnap you?

03:33.166 --> 03:34.333
(SIGHS)

03:34.416 --> 03:36.708
I don't know. I don't know.

03:38.166 --> 03:41.833
I've had a lot of time to think about it
and that's the best I've come up with.

03:42.416 --> 03:45.291
Either that or I'm in
the most tedious nightmare of all time.

03:45.375 --> 03:46.583
At least it was until...

03:46.666 --> 03:48.125
Until what?

03:49.166 --> 03:50.958
Uh, nothing. Nothing.

03:51.458 --> 03:52.458
(SIGHS)

03:52.541 --> 03:56.041
Listen, Prince Chauncey McSleazoid
or whatever your name is,

03:56.541 --> 03:58.083
I don't know what you're used to back home

03:58.166 --> 03:59.791
but I'm not a palace ditz
gonna go all quivery

03:59.875 --> 04:01.500
just 'cause you bat your eyes
at my direction.

04:01.583 --> 04:03.458
Oh, yeah... No.
I didn't think that you were...

04:03.541 --> 04:07.083
What? That I'd be the damsel in distress
in your sicko fantasy?

04:07.166 --> 04:08.958
- No!
- WOMAN: Little witty banter,

04:09.041 --> 04:11.333
casual innuendo or two, see if I'm game.

04:11.416 --> 04:12.875
Then you confess some insecurity.

04:12.958 --> 04:16.000
"Hey, he's got depth,
empathy, good listener too."

04:16.083 --> 04:18.458
And before we know it,
we're rolling in the hay.

04:18.541 --> 04:19.791
Okay, no. I-I-I...

04:19.875 --> 04:22.916
I've been down that path enough to know
it doesn't lead anywhere I wanna go.

04:23.000 --> 04:24.958
All I'm interested in
is getting out of here.

04:28.333 --> 04:31.416
Airk is my name.

04:31.500 --> 04:32.833
Couldn't care less.

04:32.916 --> 04:35.458
(SIGHS) And I'm actually
seeing someone so...

04:35.541 --> 04:36.750
Good for you.

04:36.833 --> 04:38.416
Yeah. Yeah, yeah. She's great.

04:38.500 --> 04:40.125
She's... She works in the...

04:41.291 --> 04:42.458
(SIGHS)

04:42.541 --> 04:43.791
Look, listen.

04:44.791 --> 04:47.000
I wanna get outta here
every bit as much as you do

04:47.083 --> 04:48.791
but I'm pretty sure
that we're trapped here

04:48.875 --> 04:50.708
until the things
that brought us here come back.

04:52.000 --> 04:53.083
You saw 'em?

04:56.583 --> 04:57.583
Monsters.

05:00.000 --> 05:02.208
But I haven't seen anybody
since I got here.

05:03.333 --> 05:05.958
- Except for you.
- And you've tried to leave?

05:06.041 --> 05:09.250
I did. I walked for days or weeks.

05:10.875 --> 05:12.500
(SIGHS)

05:12.958 --> 05:14.833
But somehow the city...

05:14.916 --> 05:18.041
- It just... It... It brought m...
- (VOICE ECHOING)

05:19.375 --> 05:20.375
What?

05:22.041 --> 05:23.208
Kit!

05:25.500 --> 05:26.500
Hold on!

05:32.583 --> 05:37.416
ELORA: <i>Vantage abhor turmach!</i>
<i>Vantage abhor turmach!</i>

05:38.791 --> 05:39.791
AIRK: Kit!

05:39.916 --> 05:41.625
<i>- Vantage abhor turmach!</i>
- Kit!

05:41.708 --> 05:42.958
<i>- Vantage abhor turmach!</i>
- Kit!

05:43.041 --> 05:45.708
<i>Vantage abhor turmach!</i>

05:45.791 --> 05:48.625
<i>Vantage abhor turmach!</i>

05:49.708 --> 05:50.750
(SPLASHING)

05:50.833 --> 05:51.875
(GASPS)

05:53.708 --> 05:55.541
- JADE: Kit!
- (COUGHING)

05:55.625 --> 05:56.666
- (PANTING)
- JADE: It's okay.

05:56.750 --> 05:58.666
I got you. I got you.

05:59.625 --> 06:01.000
You're alive. It's okay.

06:02.416 --> 06:04.500
- (KIT COUGHS)
- JADE: Come on.

06:04.625 --> 06:06.666
- (KIT GRUNTS)
- (CRASHING)

06:06.750 --> 06:07.791
GRAYDON: Come on!

06:10.375 --> 06:13.583
(CRASHING)

06:28.541 --> 06:31.500
(KIT PANTING)

06:39.166 --> 06:40.416
(WILLOW SIGHS)

06:56.833 --> 06:58.208
You should try it.

06:58.291 --> 07:00.291
- What?
- See if it works.

07:01.333 --> 07:02.375
Oh, you mean, just...

07:03.333 --> 07:04.375
No, no, no. (LAUGHS)

07:05.166 --> 07:07.416
You don't do a thing like that
just casually.

07:08.041 --> 07:09.583
Demands the perfect moment,

07:10.666 --> 07:15.666
like charging into the cave of a serpent,
or facing down a horde of Death Dealers.

07:17.500 --> 07:20.958
Visiting your mother after
you haven't seen her for, like, two years.

07:21.958 --> 07:23.916
I should really check up on my mother.

07:28.375 --> 07:30.750
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

07:36.083 --> 07:37.666
WILLOW: The Shattered Sea.

07:37.750 --> 07:41.125
Where the maps end
and our final test begins.

07:42.166 --> 07:43.208
ELORA: What's the test?

07:44.291 --> 07:46.000
We have to walk across it.

07:47.625 --> 07:48.625
Do we, though?

07:48.708 --> 07:51.375
'Cause no one who's gone out
there's actually ever come ever back.

07:51.458 --> 07:54.958
Crossing the sea is the only way
to reach the Immemorial City.

07:55.041 --> 07:56.333
So let's go.

07:56.416 --> 07:57.791
No.

07:57.875 --> 07:59.041
You need to rest.

07:59.125 --> 08:00.208
I'm good.

08:02.208 --> 08:03.291
(SNIFFLES)

08:07.625 --> 08:08.833
(SIGHS)

08:08.916 --> 08:10.041
JADE: (ECHOING) Kit.

08:10.125 --> 08:11.708
(PANTING)

08:11.791 --> 08:13.541
JADE: I think
we can all do with some rest.

08:15.041 --> 08:16.375
GRAYDON: We need to resupply.

08:17.125 --> 08:19.916
Food and water, dry out somewhere.

08:21.250 --> 08:24.208
(SEABIRDS CAWING)

08:25.166 --> 08:29.541
(DOOR CREAKING)

08:36.333 --> 08:37.375
GRAYDON: Hello?

08:39.208 --> 08:40.416
Anybody home?

08:42.625 --> 08:43.625
Hello?

08:45.291 --> 08:46.416
Anybody here?

08:46.916 --> 08:47.958
(SNIFFLES)

08:48.208 --> 08:49.250
I'm fine.

08:50.958 --> 08:53.791
Just... (SIGHS) lost my balance.

08:59.833 --> 09:03.416
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

09:08.583 --> 09:11.000
I guess there are worse ways to go.

09:14.125 --> 09:15.125
- What?
- (SCREAMS)

09:15.208 --> 09:17.583
- (GASPS)
- ELORA: Oh, God.

09:17.666 --> 09:18.750
I am dreaming

09:18.833 --> 09:22.666
- and you are figments of my imagination.
- (SIGHS)

09:23.333 --> 09:25.500
- Afraid not.
- Prove it.

09:27.000 --> 09:28.166
JADE: Prove that we're real?

09:28.750 --> 09:30.125
(LAUGHS)

09:30.208 --> 09:31.583
You can't, can you?

09:32.708 --> 09:36.041
Or perhaps
I'm a figment of your imagination.

09:36.125 --> 09:41.041
Or we're all phantoms in the dream
of some vindictive god

09:41.125 --> 09:43.708
suffering from a spot of indigestion.

09:43.791 --> 09:45.875
(LAUGHING)

09:46.958 --> 09:48.416
(MAN GRUNTS, FARTS)

09:48.500 --> 09:50.833
- MAN: Whoa! (LAUGHS)
- BOORMAN: There you go. Yeah. Easy now.

09:52.208 --> 09:55.375
- MAN: Ah. Liberating, isn't it?
- BOORMAN: What?

09:55.458 --> 09:56.958
That it doesn't matter.

09:58.041 --> 10:00.291
Nothing matters.

10:01.708 --> 10:03.083
You have coin?

10:03.875 --> 10:09.125
I have gold, some gems,
diamonds, sapphires, rubies.

10:10.000 --> 10:12.416
And we've never once stayed
at a decent inn.

10:14.125 --> 10:15.666
- (THUDS)
- (CREATURE SCREECHES)

10:15.750 --> 10:17.833
- (CHAINS CLINKING)
- MAN: Don't get many customers

10:17.916 --> 10:20.333
outside of colossus crab season...

10:20.750 --> 10:23.750
(SIGHS) and even that
isn't what it used to be.

10:23.833 --> 10:25.500
- (CREATURE BELLOWING)
- (CHAINS CLINKING)

10:25.583 --> 10:28.041
- What is that?
- That's a Mudmander.

10:30.500 --> 10:32.208
(CRANKING)

10:36.291 --> 10:39.083
Zeb's silt sleigh.

10:39.166 --> 10:44.541
Available for excursions if you fancy
a tour around the many scenic coves

10:44.625 --> 10:47.458
and islets of the Eastern Coast.

10:47.541 --> 10:49.875
And, uh, what if we wanted
to take it a bit further?

10:51.000 --> 10:52.583
Turns out Willow's loaded so...

10:54.458 --> 10:55.916
Yeah, how much to buy it?

10:57.958 --> 11:00.750
(STAMMERS) Let's discuss after supper.

11:00.875 --> 11:04.166
Uh... You all look
as if you could do with a hot meal.

11:04.250 --> 11:08.666
And lucky for you, I'm an excellent cook.

11:10.208 --> 11:13.000
(SQUISHING)

11:14.750 --> 11:16.875
ZEB: (SIGHS) Sup' up, everyone.

11:19.625 --> 11:22.083
- (WORM CHITTERING)
- (SLURPING)

11:22.166 --> 11:24.333
- BOORMAN: Mmm! (SLURPING)
- WILLOW: Uh...

11:24.416 --> 11:26.625
- Do you have any salt?
- (EXCLAIMS) Salt?

11:27.458 --> 11:31.458
(ZEB FARTS, GRUMBLING)

11:36.375 --> 11:37.416
GRAYDON: Mmm.

11:39.625 --> 11:40.791
Salt.

11:40.875 --> 11:42.000
There it is.

11:42.083 --> 11:44.416
You know what, didn't even need any salt.

11:44.500 --> 11:45.791
Definitely need salt.

11:45.875 --> 11:46.916
Excuse me.

11:49.416 --> 11:50.458
(SLURPS)

11:53.750 --> 11:54.833
WILLOW: You from Cashmere?

11:56.208 --> 11:57.916
Aye. You've been?

11:58.000 --> 11:59.125
Long time ago.

11:59.208 --> 12:02.083
You ever meet a bloke there named Phil?

12:02.166 --> 12:03.583
Uh...

12:04.333 --> 12:06.625
- Not that I recall.
- Good.

12:07.333 --> 12:09.000
He's a right jackass.

12:12.166 --> 12:13.958
What are you doing out here all alone?

12:14.750 --> 12:19.041
Uh, well, I was a warrior.

12:20.291 --> 12:22.291
Paladin of Cashmere.

12:23.250 --> 12:26.583
One of three sent to rescue the princess

12:27.416 --> 12:32.958
who was taken by servants
of a dark power and whom I loved,

12:34.541 --> 12:37.666
though she was betrothed to...

12:38.958 --> 12:40.000
To who?

12:40.083 --> 12:41.916
(STAMMERING) No, no, hang on a minute.

12:43.333 --> 12:45.125
That's a different quest.

12:46.166 --> 12:49.625
- This one was to find an enchanted pool...
- (SIGHS)

12:49.708 --> 12:52.875
...that granted
whomsoever drank of its water...

12:52.958 --> 12:54.958
No, that's not the right one either.

12:55.625 --> 12:57.541
You don't know what quest you were on?

12:57.625 --> 13:01.750
(STAMMERING)
Well, all these quests and battles

13:01.833 --> 13:04.625
and aspirants vying for the throne,

13:04.708 --> 13:08.958
they sometimes sorta
all get blended together.

13:09.625 --> 13:11.125
Well, what do you remember?

13:11.458 --> 13:15.208
Ah. Years, wandering the Shattered Sea.

13:16.500 --> 13:20.291
Our boots rotting,
our swords rusting in their scabbards.

13:21.750 --> 13:26.541
Till we forgot who we were,
what we were searching for.

13:27.875 --> 13:31.958
And in the end, turned on each other.

13:33.791 --> 13:36.041
Murdered each other.

13:36.125 --> 13:39.500
(THUNDER BREAKING)

13:40.750 --> 13:42.583
What's beyond the Shattered Sea?

13:42.666 --> 13:47.791
Some say that, uh, eventually you reach
the edge of the world and get swept off.

13:47.875 --> 13:49.458
(LAUGHS)

13:49.791 --> 13:52.166
Others speak of a leviathan,

13:52.958 --> 13:58.208
so monstrous that even to see it
is to lose your mind.

13:59.750 --> 14:01.791
But the truth, I know...

14:01.875 --> 14:03.666
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

14:04.375 --> 14:05.958
There's nothing beyond.

14:08.666 --> 14:12.750
The sea goes on forever.

14:12.833 --> 14:15.166
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

14:18.708 --> 14:22.166
Just because you didn't find anything,
doesn't mean it isn't there.

14:24.791 --> 14:26.000
It is.

14:26.083 --> 14:27.583
Guess we'll find out.

14:27.666 --> 14:28.666
Yeah.

14:30.541 --> 14:31.583
We will.

14:33.166 --> 14:35.250
When I was drowning, I saw Airk.

14:35.333 --> 14:37.666
And The Crone was reaching out for him.

14:39.250 --> 14:40.875
I think he's running out of time.

14:45.166 --> 14:47.541
(WIND WHOOSHING)

14:59.333 --> 15:01.666
(GROANING)

15:09.125 --> 15:10.541
(GROANS)

15:12.500 --> 15:13.916
Hey, new girl!

15:14.916 --> 15:15.958
Where you at?

15:17.000 --> 15:18.000
(SIGHS)

15:35.500 --> 15:37.500
(PANTING)

15:40.833 --> 15:43.750
(VOICES ECHOING)

15:48.875 --> 15:52.750
WOMAN: This is incredible. (GASPS)

15:54.833 --> 15:57.291
- Come on, let's go.
- Why? What's down there?

15:57.958 --> 15:59.250
I don't know, I just...

15:59.333 --> 16:02.500
(VOICES ECHOING)

16:02.583 --> 16:04.333
I just know that we shouldn't be here.

16:04.416 --> 16:05.833
What if it's the way out?

16:06.208 --> 16:07.333
The only way out.

16:07.416 --> 16:09.250
It's not, okay?

16:11.208 --> 16:13.791
But how can we know until we try?

16:17.333 --> 16:18.541
AIRK: Do whatever you want.

16:25.666 --> 16:27.958
Wait! I'm sorry.

16:29.791 --> 16:31.291
- (GASPS)
- (SLAMS)

16:32.125 --> 16:34.416
Just please...

16:38.250 --> 16:40.708
don't go down those steps.

16:43.541 --> 16:45.083
WOMAN: I won't. I promise.

16:48.416 --> 16:49.500
It was just...

16:50.583 --> 16:51.625
What?

16:54.500 --> 16:56.875
(AIRK GASPING)

17:03.083 --> 17:04.208
(SIGHING)

17:07.041 --> 17:09.500
I think, maybe, I know why we're here.

17:11.125 --> 17:12.916
How much do you know about Cashmere?

17:13.000 --> 17:14.500
Just what everybody knows.

17:14.583 --> 17:19.625
The Paladin Circle, Ivory Tower,
streets lined with moonstones.

17:19.708 --> 17:20.833
It's very beautiful.

17:21.666 --> 17:24.250
High walls that keep us safe, isolated.

17:25.375 --> 17:26.416
There are rules,

17:27.083 --> 17:29.750
and so long as you follow them,
you'll never want for anything.

17:30.958 --> 17:32.041
Except...

17:33.333 --> 17:34.583
What?

17:34.666 --> 17:36.541
There were rumors of a secret sect

17:36.625 --> 17:39.166
that worshipped
some sort of ancient blood magic

17:40.333 --> 17:41.916
called The Order of the Wyrm.

17:43.291 --> 17:45.250
Their acts of sedition were small,
at first.

17:45.333 --> 17:49.291
Desecrations, fires,
crimes without culprits

17:50.375 --> 17:52.291
but they'd always leave their mark.

17:52.416 --> 17:54.750
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

17:54.833 --> 17:56.833
One night,
they fought their way into the tower,

17:56.916 --> 17:58.958
killing the guards
and kidnapping the princess.

17:59.041 --> 18:00.833
Why? To what end? To seize power?

18:00.916 --> 18:02.625
Maybe. I don't know.

18:04.541 --> 18:05.625
I woke up here.

18:09.625 --> 18:11.666
You were merciless
when I told you I was a prince!

18:11.750 --> 18:13.208
- You were snotty about it.
- No!

18:13.291 --> 18:16.166
"I'm the prince of Tir Asleen.
Wanna scrub some laundry on my abs?"

18:16.250 --> 18:18.916
Uh, actually, I didn't...
First of all, I don't sound like that.

18:19.000 --> 18:20.916
- Yeah, you kinda do.
- Second of all... I kinda don't.

18:21.000 --> 18:23.208
Yeah, you do
but you're less obnoxious than I expected.

18:26.166 --> 18:29.791
- Still not gonna make out or whatever.
- I hadn't even thought about it.

18:29.875 --> 18:32.125
Of course you have.
You're thinking about it right now.

18:35.666 --> 18:37.791
(SEABIRDS CAWING)

18:42.458 --> 18:45.291
(SNORING)

18:47.541 --> 18:49.041
ZEB: Breakfast, anyone?

18:49.125 --> 18:51.958
I can knock you up some eggs, no problem.

18:52.250 --> 18:53.291
(CRACKING)

18:54.500 --> 18:58.458
Well, we'll take any food you can spare
but we have to get moving.

18:59.125 --> 19:01.041
What? Where?

19:01.916 --> 19:03.458
Beyond the Shattered Sea.

19:03.541 --> 19:06.750
You're in no fit condition
to be going anywhere.

19:06.833 --> 19:08.083
Neither is the peck.

19:08.916 --> 19:10.708
Stay, recuperate.

19:11.666 --> 19:12.958
You okay?

19:13.125 --> 19:15.041
ZEB: Oh. Rough weather coming on.

19:15.125 --> 19:16.541
Best wait it out.

19:18.083 --> 19:20.666
BOORMAN: (CLEARS THROAT)
You know what? Maybe he's right.

19:20.750 --> 19:23.333
I mean, I don't know,
what's one more day when you're gonna be

19:23.416 --> 19:26.708
trudging across the Shattered Sea
for, you know, ever.

19:27.916 --> 19:28.958
KIT: That's fine.

19:30.375 --> 19:31.458
You can stay.

19:32.500 --> 19:34.000
We don't need you.

19:34.083 --> 19:35.791
Well, who likes theirs scrambled?

19:35.875 --> 19:37.041
(GRUNTS)

19:38.041 --> 19:39.500
You could've just said poached.

19:39.583 --> 19:41.208
We gotta get out of here right now!

19:41.291 --> 19:43.708
- (CREAKING)
- (THE DAG SCREECHING)

19:48.041 --> 19:49.083
GRAYDON: Aw, not again!

19:52.416 --> 19:53.458
Come on, get up!

19:53.541 --> 19:55.000
Quick! Get on the thingy.

19:55.083 --> 19:56.125
Move, you idiots!

19:57.250 --> 19:58.916
(CRASHES)

20:00.583 --> 20:02.458
- (MUDMANDER SCREECHING)
- Hyah! Hyah!

20:03.166 --> 20:04.208
Hyah!

20:04.833 --> 20:07.250
- Hyah!
- (HORSE APPROACHING)

20:07.333 --> 20:08.833
Fly, mud creature.

20:08.916 --> 20:10.333
Fly like the wind.

20:11.250 --> 20:13.625
(THE DAG SCREECHING)

20:15.916 --> 20:17.750
Don't worry. Papa's got a harpoon.

20:23.958 --> 20:25.166
- Faster!
- (GRUNTS)

20:25.250 --> 20:26.750
(WHIRRING)

20:29.583 --> 20:31.000
Huh? (GASPS)

20:31.083 --> 20:32.250
(CHITTERING)

20:32.333 --> 20:34.416
JADE: Boorman, the Lux! Try it!

20:34.500 --> 20:36.000
- No!
- Why not?

20:36.083 --> 20:38.916
Because there's a perfect moment for that.
This isn't it.

20:39.791 --> 20:41.083
(GASPS)

20:42.041 --> 20:43.083
(SCREAMS)

20:44.750 --> 20:46.958
- Elora, the wand!
- What do I do?

20:47.041 --> 20:50.208
All your feelings of love, dedication,
and devotion, gather them up and...

20:50.291 --> 20:52.125
<i>Furrochk lithrak!</i>

20:52.208 --> 20:53.250
Close.

21:00.625 --> 21:02.083
(SNARLNG)

21:02.166 --> 21:03.916
(BOTH GRUNTING)

21:04.375 --> 21:05.500
<i>Furrochk lithrak!</i>

21:06.125 --> 21:07.125
Get off, Boorman!

21:10.000 --> 21:11.000
(GROANS)

21:15.791 --> 21:17.458
Whoa. (GRUNTS)

21:18.166 --> 21:19.333
(THE DOOM CHITTERING)

21:19.833 --> 21:21.875
(BOORMAN GRUNTING)

21:23.916 --> 21:25.208
Get rid of him, Boorman!

21:25.958 --> 21:27.291
(GRUNTING)

21:31.083 --> 21:32.166
(SCREECHES)

21:35.791 --> 21:37.083
<i>Va-nu expartre!</i>

21:38.458 --> 21:39.541
(SCREECHES)

21:39.625 --> 21:42.125
- (EXPLOSION)
- (LAUGHS)

21:42.208 --> 21:44.083
- (SNARLS)
- (GROANS)

21:47.500 --> 21:48.833
GRAYDON: Elora, no!

21:49.791 --> 21:50.791
Elora!

21:50.875 --> 21:52.166
(RASPY GRUNT)

21:52.250 --> 21:53.916
(VOICE ECHOING)

21:54.000 --> 21:55.500
(STABS)

21:55.583 --> 21:56.666
(GRUNTS)

22:06.625 --> 22:07.958
(SOFTLY) She's coming for me.

22:12.541 --> 22:14.958
(CHAINS CLINKING)

22:20.083 --> 22:21.125
(GROANS)

22:21.208 --> 22:22.708
JADE: Did I ever tell you about that time

22:22.791 --> 22:25.708
when I thought I caught a possum
but it turned out to be a porcupine?

22:25.791 --> 22:27.833
And they had to pull, like,
30 quills from my foot.

22:27.916 --> 22:29.291
You said it was like three.

22:29.375 --> 22:31.583
No, it was definitely more than three.

22:31.666 --> 22:33.583
The point is,
every time they yanked one out,

22:33.666 --> 22:36.541
they used the same fool-proof method
to numb the pain.

22:39.000 --> 22:40.041
Ow!

22:40.125 --> 22:41.666
(SCREAMS) Ow!

22:42.500 --> 22:44.375
BOORMAN:
And this is where it gets really crazy.

22:44.458 --> 22:46.041
So I was like, "Move in." (LAUGHS)

22:46.125 --> 22:48.083
And she was like,
"Do you want me to move in?"

22:48.166 --> 22:51.625
And I was like, "You know, I...
If you wanna move in, you can move in."

22:51.708 --> 22:52.875
But, you see, you know, really,

22:52.958 --> 22:55.333
I think she could tell
that I didn't want her to move in, so...

22:56.000 --> 22:57.250
GRAYDON: We need to stop.

22:57.333 --> 23:00.958
This Mudmander thing is listless.

23:01.041 --> 23:06.125
It's gotta rest or do whatever Mudmanders
do to get their oomph back.

23:06.833 --> 23:08.166
Same as us, pal.

23:08.875 --> 23:09.916
They mate.

23:13.833 --> 23:16.750
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

23:19.458 --> 23:20.875
(MUDMANDER GRUNTING)

23:20.958 --> 23:24.458
GRAYDON: All right, come on, time to eat.

23:26.333 --> 23:30.125
If you wouldn't mind,
not biting the hand that feeds you.

23:32.541 --> 23:34.958
That's it. It's okay.

23:35.041 --> 23:37.666
(GRUNTING)

23:38.750 --> 23:40.125
(CHITTERS)

23:40.208 --> 23:41.458
Aw!

23:44.916 --> 23:46.666
I shall name you Kenneth,

23:46.750 --> 23:49.833
after the protagonist
of the romantic farce I'm writing.

23:49.916 --> 23:51.916
(PURRING)

23:52.000 --> 23:54.583
That was impressive what you did today.

23:54.666 --> 23:56.375
What was that you were using?

23:56.458 --> 23:57.458
Oh.

23:58.500 --> 23:59.625
Just my flute.

24:01.125 --> 24:02.708
You know, it was... it was instinct.

24:02.791 --> 24:05.083
Just from listening to you and Elora.

24:05.708 --> 24:09.750
Meaningful objects can be conduits,
but the magic's in you.

24:11.791 --> 24:12.833
ELORA: Hey.

24:13.958 --> 24:15.083
Time to train.

24:18.500 --> 24:20.375
So, what happened earlier? On the sleigh?

24:21.208 --> 24:22.750
- I froze.
- Why?

24:25.625 --> 24:27.833
- Doesn't matter.
- So, what do you do?

24:29.000 --> 24:32.583
Take all the love and crap
in the center of my chest,

24:32.666 --> 24:34.625
let it build up,
and then shoot it out of my wand.

24:34.708 --> 24:35.750
WILLOW: All right.

24:35.833 --> 24:38.083
(CHIMING)

24:40.541 --> 24:42.375
You know, your opponent
won't tell you when to...

24:42.458 --> 24:44.000
<i>- Kathoth lunanore!</i>
- (THUDS)

24:44.083 --> 24:45.708
(GROANS)

24:45.791 --> 24:47.375
(PANTING)

24:48.916 --> 24:50.625
(GASPING)

24:50.708 --> 24:51.708
WILLOW: Good.

24:52.375 --> 24:54.750
So, what did we learn?

24:55.416 --> 24:57.000
That you're a little mean?

24:57.083 --> 24:58.166
WILLOW: Sure.

24:58.250 --> 25:00.750
Also, you have to learn
to defend before you attack.

25:01.416 --> 25:05.666
A simple buckler spell, <i>hither tuatha,</i>
should repel most hexes.

25:05.750 --> 25:08.000
And, as with all magic,
you have to mean it.

25:09.500 --> 25:14.916
Remember, simplicity, intention,
and, most importantly, the breath.

25:15.000 --> 25:20.333
(BOTH BREATHING DEEPLY)

25:20.416 --> 25:21.416
Centered.

25:22.500 --> 25:24.291
<i>Avalorium lanoosh!</i>

25:24.375 --> 25:25.416
<i>Hither tuatha!</i>

25:28.750 --> 25:29.791
Missed.

25:29.875 --> 25:32.458
In battle against an opponent
who means you real harm,

25:32.541 --> 25:35.166
you have to be prepared for anything.

25:36.583 --> 25:37.666
(GASPS)

25:40.375 --> 25:41.375
(CRACKLING)

25:43.208 --> 25:44.416
(STRAINING)

25:46.666 --> 25:48.541
- (GRUNTING)
- (THUDS)

25:52.916 --> 25:54.291
(GROANS)

25:58.708 --> 26:01.083
(PANTING)

26:01.166 --> 26:02.208
Get up.

26:07.500 --> 26:08.541
(GRUNTS)

26:09.750 --> 26:11.583
(ENERGETIC MUSIC PLAYING)

26:11.666 --> 26:12.708
Come with me.

26:13.375 --> 26:14.416
Okay.

26:14.833 --> 26:15.875
Where we goin'?

26:18.958 --> 26:21.125
You wanna spar? Now?

26:21.208 --> 26:24.083
Elora isn't the only one
that needs to get ready for a fight.

26:26.000 --> 26:29.583
This time, don't you dare hold back.

26:33.958 --> 26:35.833
(BOTH GRUNTING)

26:42.541 --> 26:44.083
Come on, focus.

26:44.166 --> 26:46.791
Not on your petty rivalries,
but on what you're doing.

26:47.500 --> 26:48.666
(GRUNTS)

26:55.250 --> 26:56.250
(ELORA GRUNTS)

26:56.333 --> 26:57.375
(THUDS)

27:04.000 --> 27:06.833
(BOTH GRUNTING)

28:16.833 --> 28:17.833
(MUSIC STOPS)

28:18.916 --> 28:20.291
I know what you're doing.

28:20.875 --> 28:22.000
What's that?

28:22.083 --> 28:23.083
Minetta's Ploy.

28:24.333 --> 28:26.666
(BOTH GRUNTING)

28:28.875 --> 28:33.083
Your opponent thinks that they know you,
thinks they can anticipate your next move.

28:33.750 --> 28:36.125
But you keep frustrating
those expectations.

28:36.541 --> 28:39.375
(BOTH GRUNTING)

28:39.666 --> 28:40.666
(EXHALES)

28:41.208 --> 28:42.750
Sounds pretty frustrating.

28:42.833 --> 28:44.166
(BOTH GRUNTING)

28:44.250 --> 28:46.333
JADE: Yeah, can be frustrating.

28:46.416 --> 28:49.708
Especially if you've been, like,
aching to fight them for a while now,

28:49.791 --> 28:52.250
but circumstances
keep denying them the opportunity.

28:54.000 --> 28:55.833
Maybe forces them to make a mistake,

28:55.916 --> 28:59.708
or leaves them vulnerable
to something unexpected.

29:00.875 --> 29:03.000
(JADE GRUNTING)

29:03.666 --> 29:05.583
- That's the strategy.
- I love you.

29:05.708 --> 29:07.625
(GASPING)

29:07.708 --> 29:09.375
(PANTING)

29:11.166 --> 29:12.250
You fight dirty.

29:13.208 --> 29:14.250
About time.

29:14.333 --> 29:16.458
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

29:16.541 --> 29:17.833
I really do...

29:20.083 --> 29:21.083
love you.

29:22.333 --> 29:23.333
Yeah?

29:24.291 --> 29:25.333
Yeah.

29:26.666 --> 29:28.625
Then shut up and do something about it.

29:34.041 --> 29:35.458
(JADE MOANS)

29:48.166 --> 29:49.625
You are still holding back.

29:49.708 --> 29:51.666
You've gotta dig deeper.

29:51.750 --> 29:54.000
Use your emotions, your imagination.

29:54.083 --> 29:55.416
You wanna defeat the Crone?

29:55.500 --> 29:57.583
Well, go on, show me.
What are you waiting for?

29:57.666 --> 29:59.250
- Stop it.
- What?

30:00.125 --> 30:01.166
(THUDS)

30:01.458 --> 30:03.416
(PANTING) Baiting me.

30:03.500 --> 30:04.541
It won't work.

30:04.625 --> 30:06.416
What, and denying your feelings will?

30:06.500 --> 30:08.708
I... I don't wanna hurt you.

30:08.791 --> 30:10.166
What do you want?

30:10.250 --> 30:11.708
- To... To save Airk.
- Why?

30:12.125 --> 30:13.125
(THUDS)

30:13.791 --> 30:15.083
Because I love him.

30:15.166 --> 30:16.458
What do you love about him?

30:17.666 --> 30:19.625
His cute smile? That he's a prince?

30:19.708 --> 30:23.250
Or maybe because all the other girls
wanted him and he picked you.

30:23.333 --> 30:24.500
He was kind to me.

30:24.583 --> 30:27.250
WILLOW: What, and no one else
has ever been kind to you before?

30:27.333 --> 30:29.583
No stable boy has ever smiled back?

30:30.250 --> 30:31.916
What do you want me to say?

30:32.000 --> 30:34.166
Your doubt, jealousy, pride, hunger.

30:34.250 --> 30:36.375
Accept those parts of yourself,

30:36.458 --> 30:38.916
'cause it's the only way
you'll ever master them.

30:39.000 --> 30:40.666
I want you to be honest.

30:40.750 --> 30:43.208
(HOARSELY) <i>Fungi yuggoth.</i>

30:43.291 --> 30:44.291
<i>Fungi yuggoth.</i>

30:48.250 --> 30:50.083
Willow! No!

30:51.291 --> 30:53.166
(PANTING) Willow! Willow!

30:54.041 --> 30:56.833
(GROANING)

31:02.083 --> 31:03.416
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

31:03.500 --> 31:06.583
BOORMAN: Dare I ask, how do we know
we're even going in the right direction?

31:10.333 --> 31:13.750
Has anyone else noticed the days getting
longer and the nights getting shorter?

31:15.750 --> 31:16.833
Yes.

31:16.916 --> 31:19.041
(SIGHS) Also, we're running out of food.

31:19.125 --> 31:20.750
- BOORMAN: Uh-huh.
- Wanna turn back?

31:20.833 --> 31:22.958
- BOORMAN: Yep, I do.
- No.

31:26.000 --> 31:28.958
That spell you used on me,
it was Pnakotic.

31:29.041 --> 31:30.291
Was it?

31:30.375 --> 31:31.416
Yeah.

31:31.833 --> 31:32.958
Where'd you learn that?

31:34.625 --> 31:35.875
At Nockmaar.

31:36.291 --> 31:37.375
In the Malatrium.

31:38.208 --> 31:40.500
WILLOW: The Crone's feared you
since before you were born.

31:40.583 --> 31:43.416
She'll try and weaken your resolve,
manipulate you.

31:43.500 --> 31:47.208
- How?
- Not really any of your concern, is it?

31:47.291 --> 31:48.625
It is if she succeeds.

31:50.375 --> 31:51.750
Just get me where we're going.

31:52.875 --> 31:53.916
And then what?

31:55.250 --> 31:56.791
I'll kill the witch.

31:56.875 --> 31:58.541
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

32:08.458 --> 32:09.916
WOMAN: I wasn't happy.

32:10.000 --> 32:12.000
- Why not?
- I should've been.

32:12.791 --> 32:14.333
I had everything I could ever want,

32:14.416 --> 32:19.291
none of it could squelch this nagging
feeling that something was wrong.

32:19.375 --> 32:20.458
With what?

32:22.083 --> 32:23.291
Cashmere.

32:23.375 --> 32:27.958
These rules we obeyed,
what was okay to think, to say, to want.

32:28.916 --> 32:30.875
What if I wanted something else?

32:30.958 --> 32:32.791
Something that wasn't permitted?

32:32.875 --> 32:34.166
Or safe?

32:34.250 --> 32:37.125
Well, you shouldn't do things
just because they're expected of you.

32:37.208 --> 32:38.791
You don't do what's expected of you?

32:40.291 --> 32:41.833
Nothing's expected of me.

32:42.500 --> 32:44.541
- So what are you gonna do?
- AIRK: I don't know.

32:45.666 --> 32:47.541
Marry Dove, start a family.

32:47.625 --> 32:49.541
- Dove?
- Her real name's BrÃ¼nhilde.

32:49.625 --> 32:51.250
- I just call her Dove.
- Right.

32:51.333 --> 32:52.666
Then defend the realm.

32:52.750 --> 32:57.666
You know, defend the realm
and just be the best brother,

32:57.750 --> 33:00.958
and husband, and father,
and son that I can possibly be.

33:01.041 --> 33:04.375
Because that is what you do
when you have honor, right?

33:05.125 --> 33:07.375
- What do you want?
- To be free.

33:07.458 --> 33:10.541
To follow my impulses,
say what I really think.

33:11.958 --> 33:13.041
You know, I...

33:17.416 --> 33:20.291
(BOTH BREATHING HEAVILY)

33:21.333 --> 33:23.333
(BREATH SHUDDERING)

33:28.083 --> 33:29.291
I can't.

33:29.375 --> 33:31.333
- Right, that was dumb.
- I can't.

33:31.416 --> 33:32.875
- No.
- I'm sorry.

33:33.916 --> 33:35.625
No, no, no, don't be. Don't be.

33:36.291 --> 33:38.500
- I... I really do love...
- Dove.

33:38.583 --> 33:39.666
Yes, yes.

33:40.625 --> 33:44.000
Yes, and I have to get back to her.

33:47.083 --> 33:50.750
I think maybe I know a way
you can go home.

33:55.000 --> 33:56.708
I was here before you got here.

33:57.875 --> 33:59.416
I've actually been here a long time.

34:01.041 --> 34:04.250
I hid from you because I've made mistakes.

34:05.083 --> 34:06.500
I trusted the wrong person,

34:06.583 --> 34:09.083
and I had to be sure
that I could trust you.

34:10.708 --> 34:12.000
I was like you once,

34:12.625 --> 34:16.000
trapped by my fears
and the lies I had to unlearn.

34:16.083 --> 34:20.125
You are the one that brought me here.

34:20.208 --> 34:23.083
- You're freaking out.
- Yes, I am. A little.

34:23.166 --> 34:24.416
It's natural.

34:24.500 --> 34:25.791
It's how it always starts.

34:25.875 --> 34:26.916
What?

34:27.000 --> 34:30.708
You think know
what is real and what isn't,

34:32.125 --> 34:34.500
what is light, and what is dark,

34:35.625 --> 34:37.791
what is good, and what is evil.

34:37.875 --> 34:39.250
Oh, my God.

34:39.333 --> 34:43.625
Now forget all you know or think you know,

34:44.833 --> 34:46.000
and come with me.

34:58.791 --> 35:00.375
KIT: I heard my father's voice.

35:01.833 --> 35:03.166
Calling out to me.

35:03.833 --> 35:04.958
When?

35:05.041 --> 35:06.333
Beyond the seal.

35:07.708 --> 35:08.916
In the light.

35:20.333 --> 35:21.375
What is the Wyrm?

35:27.166 --> 35:29.708
If magic is the bloodstream
of the universe,

35:31.000 --> 35:33.000
the Wyrm feeds on it.

35:33.666 --> 35:37.916
Imprisoned a long time ago
beneath the surface of world,

35:38.000 --> 35:40.916
it waits, sleeping.

35:43.166 --> 35:44.416
When it wakes up?

35:52.416 --> 35:55.333
(SCREAMS ECHOING)

35:56.333 --> 36:00.750
Da! I really need you right now.

36:00.833 --> 36:03.291
I wasn't strong enough to keep him out.

36:03.958 --> 36:05.291
(SOBBING) Please.

36:05.375 --> 36:06.583
BOORMAN: Wake up!

36:06.666 --> 36:08.833
- (GASPING)
- (GROANING)

36:11.500 --> 36:12.916
I'm sorry. You were dreaming.

36:14.250 --> 36:15.250
It wasn't a dream.

36:15.958 --> 36:17.166
I've been having them too.

36:18.000 --> 36:20.000
Same one over and over.

36:20.083 --> 36:21.208
What's yours?

36:21.291 --> 36:23.708
I'm at this wedding. I'm completely naked.

36:24.791 --> 36:26.083
Everyone's laughing at me.

36:26.833 --> 36:28.166
Which doesn't make any sense

36:28.250 --> 36:30.875
'cause, you know,
I look phenomenal, you know, naked.

36:31.583 --> 36:34.500
- And I've got really gorgeous...
- All right, don't say any more.

36:39.708 --> 36:44.041
(PURRING)

36:54.916 --> 36:56.166
I don't know what to do.

36:58.916 --> 37:02.833
The further we go,
the more depressed he seems.

37:07.291 --> 37:08.750
I think we're getting close.

37:09.666 --> 37:10.916
You know, to the city.

37:12.041 --> 37:13.750
I think maybe he can feel it.

37:13.833 --> 37:15.291
Hey, stop it. Stop it.

37:17.416 --> 37:18.458
What?

37:18.541 --> 37:19.583
Scratching.

37:20.375 --> 37:21.791
It'll only make it worse.

37:28.958 --> 37:30.083
(SNIFFLES)

37:34.791 --> 37:40.500
I think I just wanna be alone with him
for a little while.

37:54.041 --> 37:55.125
MIMS: (ECHOING)<i> Da!</i>

37:57.958 --> 37:59.833
<i>I really need you right now.</i>

38:09.791 --> 38:11.000
How much further, you think?

38:11.083 --> 38:13.458
Look, I said we'll get there and we will.

38:14.583 --> 38:16.375
Just makin' sure you still believe it.

38:17.750 --> 38:19.333
Been out here a long time.

38:19.416 --> 38:20.500
Weeks...

38:22.250 --> 38:23.291
Months.

38:23.375 --> 38:24.958
I can't even tell anymore.

38:25.041 --> 38:26.083
Can you?

38:27.041 --> 38:28.208
No.

38:35.583 --> 38:36.916
I miss Mims.

38:40.041 --> 38:42.875
If you could talk to her right now,
what would you say?

38:44.250 --> 38:45.416
Hang on, bobbin. (SIGHS)

38:47.416 --> 38:48.583
I'll be home soon.

38:51.500 --> 38:52.625
(SOBS)

39:16.083 --> 39:17.125
You should sleep.

39:17.625 --> 39:18.708
I'm not tired.

39:19.875 --> 39:21.375
You're no good to anyone weak.

39:31.166 --> 39:32.875
I stopped you from...

39:34.541 --> 39:35.583
going after your father.

39:36.666 --> 39:37.708
(SIGHS)

39:44.791 --> 39:46.666
- But you saved my life.
- Yeah.

39:52.500 --> 39:58.041
I don't know
why Madmartigan did whatever he did.

40:02.625 --> 40:04.250
I don't even remember him.

40:06.375 --> 40:10.083
But I don't believe
that he chose me over you.

40:14.041 --> 40:17.166
And I don't believe
that he didn't love you.

40:20.000 --> 40:21.416
Completely.

40:35.250 --> 40:36.541
I was jealous of you.

40:40.041 --> 40:43.125
And not 'cause you're the Chosen One
and I'm not,

40:43.208 --> 40:49.583
but just 'cause of the way that people...

40:52.291 --> 40:54.791
Nothing I've ever wanted
has come naturally to me.

41:00.166 --> 41:01.458
What did you want?

41:03.333 --> 41:04.375
To be brave.

41:07.333 --> 41:08.416
And loved.

41:11.041 --> 41:12.625
And to not be a princess. (SIGHS)

41:13.416 --> 41:14.583
(LAUGHS)

41:15.041 --> 41:16.291
It's funny.

41:18.750 --> 41:20.000
I sort of did.

41:25.291 --> 41:27.666
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

41:36.250 --> 41:37.583
I am worthy of this.

41:41.625 --> 41:43.291
(METAL CLINKS)

41:44.291 --> 41:47.791
(THUNDER BREAKING)

41:58.916 --> 42:03.583
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

42:12.125 --> 42:15.541
- (GRUNTING)
- (THUDDING)

42:17.000 --> 42:20.583
WILLOW: <i>Danu, danu, greenan luatha.</i>

42:21.708 --> 42:24.875
(ECHOING) Mims, hear my voice.

42:25.833 --> 42:27.208
Reach out to me.

42:28.375 --> 42:29.416
MIMS: Da?

42:35.250 --> 42:37.666
Mims, are you okay?

42:37.750 --> 42:39.041
Are you safe?

42:40.000 --> 42:41.250
MIMS: I'm fine.

42:42.583 --> 42:43.708
I was so worried.

42:44.875 --> 42:45.916
I had a vision.

42:46.833 --> 42:48.458
Silas came home.

42:50.666 --> 42:51.833
Well, that's...

42:53.000 --> 42:54.208
Silas is dead.

42:56.208 --> 42:57.333
We didn't know.

42:59.416 --> 43:00.916
We let him in.

43:01.583 --> 43:03.666
You weren't there to protect us.

43:03.750 --> 43:06.458
Off on one of your adventures.

43:06.541 --> 43:08.250
Just like last time.

43:09.208 --> 43:11.333
How is your adventure, Da?

43:14.083 --> 43:15.541
Are you having fun?

43:17.250 --> 43:18.750
(GASPS)

43:18.833 --> 43:20.750
Hey, you're dreaming.
Hey, you're dreaming.

43:21.416 --> 43:23.000
- I have to go home.
- You can't.

43:24.083 --> 43:26.250
We need you. I need you.

43:26.333 --> 43:28.625
When Kiaya needed me, I wasn't there.

43:28.708 --> 43:30.875
By the time I got back, it was too late.

43:30.958 --> 43:32.583
Ranon, he blamed me.

43:32.666 --> 43:34.583
- That's why he ran away.
- (THUNDER BREAKING)

43:34.666 --> 43:36.125
Mims is all I have left.

43:36.208 --> 43:37.458
It's the Crone.

43:37.541 --> 43:39.291
She's trying to separate us

43:39.375 --> 43:41.791
because she's afraid
of what we can do if we're united.

43:41.875 --> 43:44.791
- How do you know it isn't real?
- BOORMAN: Don't you understand? Huh?

43:44.875 --> 43:47.833
- You've killed us!
- I had to do it. I didn't have a choice.

43:47.916 --> 43:49.166
What did he do?

43:49.250 --> 43:52.000
- He set Kenneth free.
- GRAYDON: He was sick!

43:52.083 --> 43:53.625
If I didn't, he was gonna die!

43:53.708 --> 43:56.000
- (SIGHS)
- BOORMAN: Yeah? Well, now we're gonna die.

43:56.083 --> 43:57.625
Hundreds of leagues from anywhere.

43:57.708 --> 44:00.541
There's no way to go forward,
there's no way to go backwards.

44:00.625 --> 44:03.625
And nothing, nothing has gone
the way it was supposed to!

44:03.708 --> 44:06.083
(BOORMAN PANTING)

44:06.166 --> 44:07.416
We have to walk.

44:09.500 --> 44:11.000
It's what you said.

44:11.083 --> 44:12.750
We walk across it.

44:13.791 --> 44:15.916
For how long? Till we starve?

44:17.791 --> 44:19.375
It's not long now.

44:19.458 --> 44:20.625
We're close.

44:24.375 --> 44:26.541
(GROANING)

44:26.791 --> 44:28.500
(SCRAPING)

44:28.583 --> 44:29.875
(DOOR SLAMS)

44:29.958 --> 44:32.000
(GROANING)

44:54.458 --> 44:57.458
(OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

45:13.708 --> 45:15.083
I'll do whatever you want.

45:15.166 --> 45:16.875
(SHUSHING)

45:19.333 --> 45:20.500
Don't be afraid.

45:23.083 --> 45:24.375
We've got you now.

45:32.166 --> 45:35.500
(WIND WHOOSHING)

45:39.750 --> 45:43.166
(ELORA PANTING)

45:43.250 --> 45:44.458
We're almost there.

45:46.333 --> 45:49.875
I didn't know
how far we'd have to go.

45:59.458 --> 46:02.166
Your mother told me before we left
that you'd never give up.

46:03.125 --> 46:06.166
And there might come a time
where I'd have to bring you home.

46:07.666 --> 46:09.000
You think this is it?

46:12.833 --> 46:13.875
No.

46:14.750 --> 46:17.166
I think you're gonna make that decision
on your own.

46:25.833 --> 46:27.291
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

46:27.375 --> 46:29.916
(WIND WHOOSHING)

46:30.000 --> 46:31.041
BOORMAN: Hey.

46:33.166 --> 46:34.583
Do you see that?

46:34.666 --> 46:36.125
What? The giant skull?

46:37.333 --> 46:38.416
Yeah.

46:38.958 --> 46:40.000
Just checking.

46:42.500 --> 46:44.208
I'm not who I thought I was, Gray.

46:45.458 --> 46:46.625
Who are you?

46:47.916 --> 46:50.208
(BOORMAN PANTING)

46:51.375 --> 46:52.458
I'm nobody.

47:10.708 --> 47:11.791
You okay?

47:16.041 --> 47:17.083
It's funny.

47:17.791 --> 47:21.458
When I was a kid,
I used to play at being a sorcerer.

47:23.166 --> 47:25.958
Visiting strange worlds,
fighting monsters.

47:27.208 --> 47:31.333
Never thought I'd actually really do it,
let alone with Elora Danan.

47:40.541 --> 47:44.291
When we get to the city,
I know you're gonna save Airk,

47:44.375 --> 47:47.166
and you two will go off together.

47:48.041 --> 47:49.416
'Cause you love him.

47:49.500 --> 47:56.125
And while I don't love him, I do love you.

47:58.541 --> 47:59.708
Graydon...

47:59.791 --> 48:00.916
It's okay.

48:01.000 --> 48:02.833
I'm not asking you to love me back.

48:02.916 --> 48:06.500
I just wanted to tell you
'cause without you,

48:06.583 --> 48:09.166
I never would've have become
the man I've always wanted be.

48:09.250 --> 48:11.250
(SOLEMN MUSIC PLAYING)

48:36.666 --> 48:37.708
- Whoa!
- (ELORA GASPS)

48:37.791 --> 48:39.083
KIT: Oh, my God.

48:39.166 --> 48:42.916
(WATERFALL CRASHING)

48:43.000 --> 48:44.166
ELORA: Impossible.

48:46.500 --> 48:48.458
Maybe we took a wrong a turn somewhere.

48:48.541 --> 48:51.125
Oh, yeah, should've gone left.

48:52.541 --> 48:55.000
We crossed the sea. We passed the test.

48:55.083 --> 48:57.250
The city is supposed to be here.

48:57.333 --> 48:58.541
It isn't.

48:58.625 --> 48:59.666
It has to be!

49:01.041 --> 49:02.208
I'm turning back.

49:03.750 --> 49:05.166
Yeah, me too.

49:07.041 --> 49:08.875
We went as far as we could, Elora.

49:10.041 --> 49:11.083
(SOFTLY) No.

49:11.166 --> 49:13.041
This isn't how it ends.

49:14.125 --> 49:15.125
How does it end?

49:19.875 --> 49:21.791
ELORA: In the Immemorial City.

49:21.875 --> 49:25.458
With the wand broken, (GASPING) and me...

49:29.083 --> 49:30.125
dead.

49:31.416 --> 49:32.458
What?

49:33.125 --> 49:35.750
It's what Willow saw in his vision
all those years ago.

49:35.833 --> 49:37.000
(BREATHING SHAKILY)

49:37.083 --> 49:40.041
The reason why Sorsha
didn't want him to train me.

49:42.666 --> 49:43.916
Tried to hide me away.

49:45.083 --> 49:47.625
'Cause if I face the Crone,
that's how it'll end.

49:48.208 --> 49:49.875
(SHUDDERS)

49:51.250 --> 49:52.375
Isn't it?

49:54.333 --> 49:55.750
How did you know?

49:58.333 --> 49:59.541
She showed me.

50:00.250 --> 50:02.875
The Crone?
You've been, what, communing with her?

50:02.958 --> 50:05.000
Great. Just great.

50:05.083 --> 50:06.583
She led us right here.

50:06.666 --> 50:08.208
WILLOW: I thought I could change it.

50:08.875 --> 50:10.416
But I'm not a great sorcerer.

50:13.125 --> 50:15.166
I'm just a farmer who got lucky.

50:15.250 --> 50:17.458
(SOBBING)

50:18.125 --> 50:20.250
And I can't keep pretending.

50:20.791 --> 50:23.083
(SOBBING) Neither can I.

50:25.166 --> 50:27.583
I don't wanna be Elora Danan.

50:30.333 --> 50:32.166
I just wanna go home.

50:33.833 --> 50:35.500
(SNIFFLES)

50:44.000 --> 50:45.041
Well, tough.

50:51.666 --> 50:52.708
You're afraid.

50:55.750 --> 50:56.791
So am I.

50:59.291 --> 51:00.625
But you know what?

51:03.541 --> 51:07.458
My fear, it doesn't get to decide.

51:09.125 --> 51:12.958
It doesn't get to, to define me.

51:15.000 --> 51:17.000
I'm not giving it the power.

51:23.125 --> 51:24.583
I'm giving it to you.

51:29.375 --> 51:34.125
I have never believed
in anything my whole life.

51:36.041 --> 51:37.125
(SOBBING)

51:37.666 --> 51:39.291
I believe in you.

51:39.375 --> 51:42.333
I don't know... I don't know what to do.

51:42.416 --> 51:43.666
Yes, you do.

51:45.750 --> 51:47.000
We both do.

51:53.291 --> 51:54.416
BOORMAN: Look around.

51:54.500 --> 51:56.958
It's over.
There is nowhere to go but back.

51:57.041 --> 51:59.125
(PANTING)

52:07.208 --> 52:09.250
- You ready?
- Yes.

52:15.458 --> 52:17.250
KIT: We'll do it together.

52:28.000 --> 52:31.875
(SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING)

52:45.708 --> 52:48.666
(SPLASHES)

52:58.833 --> 53:02.083
(COUGHING)

53:02.166 --> 53:04.708
(COUGHING)

53:04.791 --> 53:07.333
(PANTING)

53:10.083 --> 53:11.208
My lady?

53:11.750 --> 53:14.500
(PANTING)

53:34.250 --> 53:37.250
(OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

53:37.333 --> 53:40.333
(WIND WHISTLING)

54:38.791 --> 54:39.833
Ominous.

54:40.958 --> 54:42.000
Very.

54:53.291 --> 54:54.916
(THUDDING IN DISTANCE)

55:00.208 --> 55:02.041
(DOOR SCRAPING)

55:02.125 --> 55:03.291
(DOOR THUDS)

55:06.000 --> 55:07.750
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)
